      "name": "Rebels",
      "groupType": "organization",
      "tags": [],
      "members": [
        {
          "type": "character",
          "id": "mpx2158gl1jore",
          "name": "Jane Novia"
        }
      ],
      "description": "A group that hates the \"ever-watching eyes\" and wishes to bring Nervios freedom through contact with the outside world and the destruction of the eyes\n\n- Quiet / Gaining traction, trying to help people escape, close ties to smugglers.\n    \n- Truly believes they’re doing what’s best for everyone, especially the people in the town\n    \n- End goal for the rebels (assuming they know or at least believe all the towers are widely unmanned): expose the truth of the matter. Maybe they want to expose the nobles too. Most likely anti-noble if they know their history (which at least the important ones probably do)\n    \n- Probably have spies in the guards\n    \n\n- Definitely trying to find some high ups willing to help to learn more about the panopticon\n    \n\n- Often work under darkness or / and with obscuring / illusion spells\n    \n- Definitely have a tunnel system\n    \n- Strong aura of secrecy, especially in their upper ranks\n    \n- Most often help people escape the town\n    \n- Maybe offers places of solace where the eye cannot see?\n    \n- The collectivist to the guard / government’s isolationist",
      "history": "",
      "structure": "",
      "goals": "",
      "resources": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "mpw00u343kto8i",
      "storyId": "mpvmtgofdnkrh0",
      "name": "Guards",
      "groupType": "organization",
      "tags": [],
      "members": [
        {
          "type": "character",
          "id": "mpx2158gl1jore",
          "name": "Jane Novia"
        }
      ],
      "description": "The guards of Nervios\n\n- Patrolling the city 24/7 on a schedule\n    \n- Guards move around in groups \n    \n- Respected by the general population, but also slightly feared\n    \n-   \n    \n- Different types of guards\n    \n\n- Internal Guards:\n    \n\n- Less trained than other branches of military with less powerful weaponry\n    \n- Underground tunnel system connecting towers\n    \n- Guard towers around the city on the walls\n    \n\n- Towers can’t be seen into from the outside\n    \n- Citizens don’t know if a tower is manned or not\n    \n\n- Guard towers throughout the interior of city\n    \n\n- Underground tunnels connecting them\n    \n\n- Maybe they have eyes that impose crippling fear on those who don't belong? (Poisoned in 5e)\n    \n\n- Allows for fast deployment of guards to any point in the city\n    \n- Outsiders can’t see in – acts as a panopticon\n    \n\n- Maintains the peace, even if a guard isn’t in that specific tower\n    \n\n- Nicknamed “Eyes” by locals/rebellion\n    \n- Tiers of guards:\n    \n\n- Junior\n    \n- Senior\n    \n- Captain \n    \n\n- Some loyal to the King, some the Government, some the rich, sizable amount are loyal to anyone who pays money\n\n\n- Army\n    \n\n- Snipers\n    \n- Infantry\n    \n\n- Navy\n    \n\n- Warships\n    \n\n  \n\n- Watchman:\n    \n\n- Guard the walls and docks from outside threats\n    \n- Controls who enters/exits the cities\n    \n- Thoroughly inspects incoming/exiting cargo \n    \n\n- Corrupted?\n    \n\n- Some guards might use their status and position to disobey laws or take advantage of others. \n    \n\n- Creates resentment and fear of all guards\n    \n- PLOTLINE: Players start as junior guards and witness a fellow guard breaking the law. They are put into a position where they must decide between what's morally right, and the approval/protection of their peers.\n    \n\n  \n\nDamaged old tower which falls apart/players explore and find out that not all towers are functional.",
